    "description": "Taking as input one or several sets of position-specific scoring matrices, this program applies hierarchical clustering to identify clusters of similar motifs. It produces a set of trees (one per cluster) and builds branch motifs at each node of each tree by merging the matrices of all descendent nodes.",
    "documentation": [
        {
            "note": "The Web interface of the tool is documented by a manual + DEMO examples. \n\nA detailed manual for the stand-alone tool is displayed on the Unix terminal with the option -help.",
            "type": [
                "User manual"
            ],
            "url": "http://rsat.eu/"
        }
    ],
    "download": [
        {
            "note": "This tool is part of the software suite Regulatory Sequence Analysis Tools (RSAT), which can be downloaded and installed on Unix operating systems (Linux, Mac OS X). To download the tool, open a connection to any RSAT server, and follow the download link.",
